A cantilever 3D printer is a type of 3D printing machine designed with a single-sided support structure for the print bed or arm. Its compact and lightweight design allows efficient movement while reducing the overall size of the machine. The printer operates by depositing melted filament layer by layer to create three-dimensional objects with precision and accuracy. The cantilever structure provides easy access to the printing area, making maintenance and monitoring more convenient. This type of 3D printer is commonly used for educational purposes, prototyping, small-scale manufacturing, and engineering projects because of its simple design, cost efficiency, and reliable performance.
